Title: Parallel Computation of Reachable Dead States in a Free-choice Petri Net  
Author: W.M.P. van der Aalst 
Keyword: Petri nets; Parallel algorithms, Free-choice Petri nets; Analysis of Petri nets.  
Address: P.O. Box 513, 5600 MB, Eindhoven, The Netherlands,  
Affiliation: Departmentof Mathematics and ComputingScience, Eindhoven Universityof Technology,  
Abstract: Free-choice Petri nets are a prominent tool for modeling and analyzing communication protocols, multiprocessor systems, parallel programs, flexible manufacturing systems and workflow scripts. Unfortunately, analysis is often hampered by the state-explosion phenomenon. Even for free-choice Petri nets, the reachability problem is known to be EXPSPACE-hard. In this paper we discuss a technique for the parallel computation of the reachable dead states. This technique is based on the partitioning of tokens instead of the Petri net. 
